  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<p><span id="1" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #00533a;">Lace up those boots</span></p>
<p>Livigno and the surrounding Stelvio National Park provide the most stunning backdrop for long walks and hikes. Whether you're a hard-core hiker or just want to stroll around and take in the view, you'll find trails for all levels.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><span id="1" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #00533a;">Connect with nature</span><span style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #00533a;"></span></p>
<p>The Stelvio National park is a nature lovers paradise. It's actually the largest protected area in Europe, created to preserve the natural environment for generations to come. Made up of mountain ranges, glacial lakes, waterfalls, woodland, meadows and historical villages, it's a fantastic place to explore. Keep your eyes peeled for wildlife like deer, ibex, foxes and marmoys and don't forget to look up... you may be lucky enough to spot a bearded vulture or golden eagle. We love looking out for tracks and footprints to see which animals have been around. If it's plants that you're interested in, you'll want to look out for the glacial buttercups which grow high up on the mountain. </p>
<p> </p>
<p><span id="1" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #00533a;">Fun for the family</span></p>
<p>Livigno is full of adventure parks, which make a great family day out. You should visit Larix Park, a high ropes and adventure centre in the middle of the Larch Forest. It has nine different adventure routes, with something to suit all ages. You could also try Aquagrandia activity centre which has a swimming pool, slides, children's entertainment, a spa and a gym. The whole family will be happy! </p>
<p> </p>
<p><span id="1" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #00533a;">Mottolino Bike Park</span></p>
<p>If you love downhill and free ride mountain biking, or you want to give it a go, then you have to go to Mottolino Bike Park. It was specially built for riders looking to improve technique, learn new tricks and try out different jumps. If you're looking for more of a challenge you can practise your jump technique with the inflatable landing or try the downhill biking tracks.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><span id="1" style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #00533a;">Food and Drink</span></p>
<p>Try Bitto, a cheese typical of the Valtellina region. It is a semi-hard cheese which can be aged for between 40 days and three years. Enjoy the cheese with a few slices of Bresaola della Valtellina (dried Italian salt-beef) and some local Valtellina wine.</p>
<p>If you want something heartier to eat, Manfrigole is a filling dish made with buckweat pancakes stuffed with Bresaola and Casera cheese.</p>]]></thingsToDo>
